-- allium: 3
-- dflash_speculative.allium
--
-- Scope: the behavioural contract for serving Qwen3.6-27B with the
-- DFlash drafter on the 2026-q2-next branch of yarn-agentic /
-- ik_llama.cpp. DFlash (Chen, Liang, Liu 2026; arXiv 2602.06036) is
-- a block-diffusion speculative-decoding method: the drafter emits
-- a contiguous block of N candidate tokens in a single forward pass,
-- conditioned on fused hidden features extracted from layers of the
-- target model and on the last verified target token (the anchor).
-- The target then verifies the block in a single multi-position
-- forward and the longest matching prefix is committed.
--
-- This spec describes the BEHAVIOUR an implementation must
-- guarantee — feature extraction, projection-and-fuse, K/V
-- injection into draft layers, single-forward block emit, target
-- verify, prefix accept, paired state advance. It does NOT pick an
-- integration shape (port vs upstream vs sidecar — see
-- PHASE_DFLASH_SCOPING.md in mtp-agentic for option A/B/C/D).
--
-- The spec is precision-agnostic: target may run at IQ4_KS, draft
-- at BF16; only the relationships between tensors are constrained,
-- not their dtypes.
--
-- Why this spec exists: a behavioural-level contract decouples the
-- correctness argument from the integration choice. We will pick A,
-- B, C, or D after running M0 (reproduce upstream's published
-- speedup on RTX 6000 sm_75); the spec stays valid regardless.
-- `allium:propagate` against it should generate the binding
-- property tests for whichever integration we pick — most
-- importantly: same-prompt determinism per-deployment under the
-- DFlash path, given that the prior np>1 same-prompt bug remains
-- unsolved on Qwen3.6-27B.
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entities for the two models, KV caches, hidden
--     features, anchor token, draft block, verify logits, accept
--     decision.
--   - Enumerations for sampler mode, accept mode, denoising
--     schedule, feature-source policy.
--   - Contracts for ExtractFeatures, ProjectAndFuse,
--     DraftBlockEmit, TargetVerifyBlock, AcceptPrefixDecision,
--     AdvanceState.
--   - System-wide invariants binding feature dimensionality, K/V
--     injection symmetry across draft layers, block-emit
--     single-forward semantics, accept-prefix contiguity, paired KV
--     advance, embed/LM-head sharing, causal-SWA mask construction,
--     greedy-mode determinism per deployment.
--   - Open questions naming the implementation choices that
--     2026-q2-next must commit to before code lands.
--
-- Excludes:
--   - Training-time procedures (anchor-conditioned block diffusion
--     training loss). The drafter is a frozen artefact from z-lab;
--     the spec covers inference only.
--   - The DFlash drafter's internal layer composition beyond the
--     SWA mask shape and the K/V-injection contract. Drafter
--     weights are loaded as a GGUF; the spec does not constrain
--     hidden_size, layer count, or attention head count beyond
--     consistency with the loaded weights.
--   - vLLM- and SGLang-side reference impls. They inform but do
--     not constrain ik_llama.cpp's implementation; the
--     PHASE_DFLASH_SCOPING.md document records their existence.
--   - Multimodal inputs. Qwen3.6-27B is multimodal at the HF
--     config level but the production GGUF is text-only and the
--     DFlash drafter does not consume images. The speculative
--     path is text-only.
--   - The prior Qwen-provided MTP head (`--draft N` production
--     path). DFlash is an external-draft speculative-decoding
--     method; the on-target MTP head is dead under this spec.

-- ============================================================
-- External entities — runtime objects we constrain
-- ============================================================

-- A ggml tensor flowing through the speculative path. We
-- reference only its existence as a typed reference; ggml manages
-- shape and dtype.
entity Tensor {
    name: String
}

-- The target language model: Qwen3.6-27B in its current ik_llama.cpp
-- representation. Hybrid attention (linear_attention + full_attention
-- in 3:1 ratio), 64 layers, hidden 5120, 24 Q heads, 4 KV heads,
-- vocab 248320, n_ctx_train 262144. The spec references only the
-- properties the speculative path actually touches.
entity TargetModel {
    n_layers:         Integer    -- 64 for Qwen3.6-27B
    hidden_size:      Integer    -- 5120
    n_kv_heads:       Integer    -- 4 (GQA ratio 6 with 24 Q heads)
    vocab_size:       Integer    -- 248320
    n_ctx_train:      Integer    -- 262144
    embedding:        Tensor     -- shared with drafter
    lm_head:          Tensor     -- shared with drafter
}

-- The DFlash drafter: a small (~2B = 865M trainable + shared
-- embed/LM head ≈ 1.73 GB BF16 on disk for Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash) DENSE
-- Qwen3 transformer. NOT a hybrid like the target: drafter layer
-- composition is strictly `full_attention` and `sliding_attention`,
-- never `linear_attention` (DeltaNet). vLLM enforces this via
-- `_DFLASH_VALID_LAYER_TYPES`; we enforce via DrafterIsDenseQwen3.
-- Reuses the target's embedding and LM head (paper §4.2). The
-- drafter's K/V projection inputs are augmented at every layer by
-- the InjectedKV produced from ProjectAndFuse (see below).
entity DraftModel {
    n_layers:         Integer
    hidden_size:      Integer    -- must equal TargetModel.hidden_size for shared embed/LM head
    n_kv_heads:       Integer
    swa_window:       Integer    -- W; causal SWA window size in tokens (per-layer; layers may differ)
    n_param:          Integer    -- ≈ 1.73 × 10^9 for Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash drafter (BF16 file size)
    layer_types:      List<DrafterLayerType>   -- per-layer; each element ∈ {full_attention, sliding_attention}
}

-- A single block of contiguous draft tokens emitted by the drafter
-- in one forward pass. Block size is configurable (default 16, vLLM
-- uses 15). Position k in the block predicts the token at
-- anchor_pos + k + 1.
entity DraftBlock {
    block_size:       Integer   -- N; default 16
    tokens:           List<Integer>   -- length N, in step order
    anchor_pos:       Integer   -- position of the anchor token in target's sequence
}

-- The hidden-feature snapshot extracted from the target at the end
-- of one target step. Features are pulled from a SUBSET of target
-- layers (uniformly sampled across depth) and fused into a single
-- compact representation via a lightweight learned projection that
-- ships with the drafter weights.
entity HiddenFeatures {
    n_source_layers:  Integer   -- size of the layer subset target was probed at
    source_indices:   List<Integer>   -- which target layer indices were sampled
    hidden_size:      Integer   -- target's hidden_size
    n_positions:      Integer   -- typically 1 (only the anchor position) but may extend
}

-- The output of the lightweight projection that maps HiddenFeatures
-- → K/V-injection tensors. This is per-draft-layer: the projection
-- emits a (K, V) pair to inject into every draft layer's attention
-- block. Stored in the draft KV cache for re-use across drafting
-- steps of the same anchor.
entity InjectedKV {
    per_draft_layer:  List<KVPair>   -- length = DraftModel.n_layers
    anchor_pos:       Integer        -- one InjectedKV is associated with one anchor
}

-- A K/V pair injected into one draft layer. Lives in the draft's KV
-- cache slot reserved for "fused-feature" content; coexists with
-- the draft's normal autoregressive K/V history at the anchor and
-- earlier accepted positions.
entity KVPair {
    k_dim_per_head:   Integer
    v_dim_per_head:   Integer
    n_kv_heads:       Integer
    n_positions:      Integer   -- typically 1 per anchor
}

-- The last verified token at which the next draft block is
-- conditioned. Anchors advance only when the target accepts.
entity AnchorToken {
    token_id:         Integer
    pos:              Integer   -- absolute position in target's sequence
}

-- The target's KV cache state. Single-slot in our production
-- (np=1) deployment. Advances only by the AcceptPrefix length per
-- speculative cycle.
entity TargetKVCache {
    seq_id:           Integer   -- always 0 in np=1
    n_cells:          Integer   -- = anchor_pos + 1 after each advance
}

-- The drafter's KV cache state. Holds (a) injected K/V from the
-- current anchor's fused features and (b) the drafter's own
-- autoregressive K/V history at the anchor and previously accepted
-- positions. Advances paired with TargetKVCache.
entity DraftKVCache {
    seq_id:           Integer
    n_cells_self:     Integer   -- drafter's own KV at accepted positions
    n_cells_injected: Integer   -- injected KV slots (1 per active anchor)
}

-- The verify-batch: a single target forward over the drafted block.
-- ne[1] = block_size + 1: the anchor itself plus the N drafted
-- tokens, all in one contiguous run. The target emits one logit
-- row per input position; row k predicts the token at
-- anchor_pos + k + 1.
entity VerifyBatch {
    seq_id:           Integer
    anchor_pos:       Integer
    block_size:       Integer
    tokens:           List<Integer>   -- length block_size + 1: [anchor, t_0, ..., t_{N-1}]
}

-- The per-position logits the target emits over the verify batch.
entity VerifyLogits {
    n_positions:      Integer   -- = VerifyBatch.block_size + 1
    n_vocab:          Integer
}

-- The result of the accept test: how many drafts of the block are
-- accepted by longest-prefix match (greedy) or by rejection
-- sampling (probabilistic). bonus_token is the target's argmax (or
-- sample) at the position immediately after the last accepted
-- draft, always committed regardless of how many drafts were
-- accepted.
entity AcceptDecision {
    n_accepted:       Integer   -- 0 .. block_size
    bonus_token:      Integer
    bonus_pos:        Integer   -- = anchor_pos + n_accepted + 1
}

-- ============================================================
-- Enumerations
-- ============================================================

-- Target sampling mode at verify time. Production runs greedy
-- (temperature=0); the contract supports probabilistic for parity
-- with future server features but currently rejects it (see
-- ProbabilisticVerifyOutOfScope).
enum SamplerMode { greedy | probabilistic }

-- Accept-decision algorithm. argmax_match is the byte-deterministic
-- variant: draft k is accepted iff it equals argmax of verify
-- logits at row k. probabilistic is the Leviathan/Chen rejection
-- sampling variant, gated by SamplerMode = probabilistic.
enum AcceptMode { argmax_match | probabilistic }

-- DFlash block-diffusion denoising schedule. The published method
-- uses a single denoising step; longer schedules are admissible by
-- the architecture but not measured. The spec binds single-step
-- and treats multi-step as a future extension (OQ-DENOISE-SCHEDULE).
enum DenoiseSchedule { single_step | multi_step }

-- Feature-source policy: which target layers HiddenFeatures is
-- pulled from. trained_indices is the published method — 5 source
-- layers uniformly selected between layer 2 and the third-to-last
-- target layer, per paper §5. The drafter weights were trained
-- against specific layer outputs; using different indices at
-- inference is a correctness violation.
enum FeatureSource { trained_indices | uniform_sample | custom }

-- Per-layer attention type for the drafter. The drafter is dense
-- Qwen3; only these two types are valid. Hybrid `linear_attention`
-- is rejected at load (DrafterIsDenseQwen3).
enum DrafterLayerType { full_attention | sliding_attention }

-- ============================================================
-- Contracts
-- ============================================================

-- Extracts hidden-state features from the target after one target
-- step completes. Reads the target's residual stream at a configured
-- subset of layer indices. No effect on the target's forward path;
-- features are a side-output snapshot.
contract ExtractFeatures {
    invoke: (target: TargetModel, anchor_pos: Integer, policy: FeatureSource) -> HiddenFeatures

    @invariant SourceLayersWithinTarget
        -- Every index in HiddenFeatures.source_indices is in the
        -- range [0, target.n_layers). The implementation must
        -- reject (or assert-fail) if a configured source index is
        -- out of range.

    @invariant UniformSampleSpacing
        -- When policy = uniform_sample, source_indices are
        -- approximately evenly spaced across [0, target.n_layers).
        -- The exact subset is an implementation choice (see
        -- OQ-SOURCE-LAYERS) but must be deterministic per
        -- deployment.

    @invariant FeatureWidthMatchesTarget
        -- HiddenFeatures.hidden_size = target.hidden_size. The
        -- features are residual-stream snapshots; no projection
        -- yet.

    @invariant DeterminismPerDeployment
        -- Two ExtractFeatures invocations with identical target
        -- state at anchor_pos and identical policy produce
        -- byte-identical HiddenFeatures.
}

-- Projects HiddenFeatures via a small learned projection and emits
-- per-draft-layer K/V injection tensors. The projection weights
-- ship as part of the drafter GGUF. Result is stored in the draft
-- KV cache, indexed by the active anchor.
contract ProjectAndFuse {
    invoke: (features: HiddenFeatures, draft: DraftModel) -> InjectedKV

    @invariant FuseProjectionFcWeight
        -- The drafter weights include a learned linear `fc` of shape
        -- (num_target_layers * hidden_size, hidden_size) — 5*5120 →
        -- 5120 for Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash. This `fc` is applied FIRST,
        -- after concatenating the 5 target hidden states channel-wise
        -- and BEFORE any K/V projection. Without this `fc` the
        -- injected K/V is garbage even if every other tensor is
        -- correct. vLLM names this `model.fc` and invokes it via
        -- `combine_hidden_states` (qwen3_dflash.py:656).
        --
        -- ik_llama.cpp must load `fc` from the drafter GGUF as a
        -- regular weight; conversion must surface it with the
        -- correct shape and dtype (BF16 for z-lab/Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash).
        -- The shared embedding/lm_head are reused from the target
        -- (per SharedEmbedAndLMHead) but `fc` is drafter-exclusive.

    @invariant PerLayerArity
        -- Length of InjectedKV.per_draft_layer = draft.n_layers.
        -- Every draft layer receives a K/V injection.

    @invariant HeadShapeMatchesDraft
        -- For every KVPair in per_draft_layer:
        --   k_dim_per_head = v_dim_per_head = draft.hidden_size /
        --   draft.n_kv_heads (or whatever the drafter's loaded
        --   weights declare). The projection respects the drafter's
        --   declared head shape; it does not rebroadcast.

    @invariant KAsymmetricallyNormedVNot
        -- vLLM precompute_and_store_context_kv (qwen3_dflash.py:441-
        -- 468) shows K and V are treated asymmetrically:
        --   - Both K and V come from one fused KV-projection GEMM
        --     across all 5 drafter layers, applied to the fc-projected
        --     context state pre-RMSNorm'd by hidden_norm.
        --   - K is then per-layer K-normed (each layer's own k_norm
        --     weight).
        --   - V is NOT normed — only projected.
        --   - K is RoPE'd; V is NOT RoPE'd.
        -- Matches Qwen3 transformer architecture (q_norm + k_norm,
        -- no v_norm; standard RoPE on Q+K, not V).

    @invariant InjectedAnchorAlignment
        -- InjectedKV.anchor_pos = features.position (the position
        -- features were extracted at). The injected K/V is logically
        -- attached to this anchor; cache eviction tied to anchor
        -- advancement (see AdvanceState).

    @invariant ReuseAcrossDenoiseSteps
        -- When DenoiseSchedule = multi_step, the same InjectedKV is
        -- consumed by every denoising step of the same anchor. The
        -- projection runs once per anchor, not per denoising step.
}

-- Emits a block of candidate tokens in a single forward pass,
-- conditioned on the anchor token and the injected K/V from
-- ProjectAndFuse. Uses block diffusion: the drafter sees masked
-- positions for t_0 .. t_{N-1} and denoises them in one forward
-- (single-step) or in K forwards (multi-step; out of scope).
contract DraftBlockEmit {
    invoke: (
        draft: DraftModel,
        anchor: AnchorToken,
        injected: InjectedKV,
        draft_kv: DraftKVCache,
        block_size: Integer,
        schedule: DenoiseSchedule,
    ) -> DraftBlock

    @invariant SingleForwardPerStep
        -- The drafter produces all block_size candidate tokens
        -- from a number of forwards equal to the denoising
        -- schedule's step count. For schedule = single_step,
        -- exactly one forward. For multi_step, K forwards where
        -- K is the schedule length; out of scope for the current
        -- spec.
        --
        -- Provenance: vllm dflash.py:319 dummy_run docstring
        --   "Only one forward pass due to parallel drafting"

    @invariant QuerySpanIsOnePlusN
        -- The drafter forward's query span per request is exactly
        -- (1 + block_size) positions: 1 anchor at position 0 plus
        -- block_size mask-token positions at positions 1..N. This
        -- is the input shape vLLM's
        -- copy_and_expand_dflash_inputs_kernel writes — it places
        -- next_token_ids[i] at out_input_ids[i*(1+N)] (the anchor)
        -- and parallel_drafting_token_id at the remaining N
        -- positions of slot i's query span.
        --
        -- Implementations that emit the anchor outside the query
        -- span, or use a different per-request shape, diverge from
        -- the trained drafter and cannot share weights with vLLM's
        -- impl.
        --
        -- Provenance: vllm dflash.py:217 (num_query_per_req =
        --   1 + self.num_speculative_tokens), :246-275 (kernel
        --   call site), :246 in copy_and_expand_dflash_inputs_kernel.

    @invariant InjectionConsumedAtEveryLayer
        -- The forward consumes injected.per_draft_layer[i] at
        -- draft layer i for every i in [0, draft.n_layers). No
        -- draft layer runs without its injected K/V. Implementations
        -- that route K/V via cross-attention satisfy this contract
        -- iff the cross-attention input at every layer is exactly
        -- the projected feature for that layer.

    @invariant LayerTypeDependentMask
        -- The drafter's attention mask is per-layer-type, not a
        -- single shape across all draft layers:
        --
        --   - sliding_attention layers (4 of 5 in Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash):
        --     causal sliding-window attention. Query at position k
        --     attends to positions [max(0, k - swa_window + 1), k]
        --     within the union of (past context, current block).
        --     Window = drafter config.sliding_window (= 2048 for
        --     Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash). SWA is intrinsically causal;
        --     "non-causal sliding window" is not a coherent mask.
        --
        --   - full_attention layers (the last layer in Qwen3.6-27B-
        --     DFlash, layer index 4): bidirectional. Query at any
        --     position k attends to ALL positions in the block AND
        --     to the entire past context. This is where the block-
        --     diffusion denoising's bidirectional mixing happens —
        --     the trained model's full_attention layer sees every
        --     mask position together and produces all block_size
        --     candidate tokens in one forward.
        --
        -- Paper §4.2 (Figure 4) confirms the training-time mask:
        --   "Tokens attend bidirectionally within the same block
        --    and to the corresponding injected target context
        --    features, while attention across different blocks is
        --    disallowed."
        --
        -- vLLM PR #40898 enforces this split: dflash.py lines 397-444
        -- specialise SWA layers with causal=True attention metadata
        -- while keeping full_attention layers at causal=False.
        -- Implementations that try to use a single mask shape across
        -- all draft layers will diverge from the trained model.

    @invariant AnchorEmbeddingFromTarget
        -- The anchor token's embedding is fetched from the shared
        -- target.embedding tensor, NOT from a duplicate drafter
        -- embedding. The drafter does not own embedding weights.

    @invariant BlockSizeBindsToConfig
        -- DraftBlock.block_size = the block_size argument. The
        -- forward emits exactly block_size masked positions plus
        -- the anchor; downstream verify constructs a verify batch
        -- of length block_size + 1.

    @invariant AnchorPosPreserved
        -- DraftBlock.anchor_pos = anchor.pos. The contract
        -- preserves the anchor position so the verify path can
        -- align its KV writes.

    @invariant DeterminismPerDeployment
        -- Two DraftBlockEmit invocations with byte-identical
        -- (draft, anchor, injected, draft_kv, block_size, schedule)
        -- produce byte-identical DraftBlock under
        -- SamplerMode = greedy (i.e. argmax over draft logits at
        -- each position). This is the per-deployment determinism
        -- contract; cross-deployment with different block_size or
        -- different feature sampling indices is NOT required to be
        -- bit-stable (cf. memory entry on cross-config kernel
        -- batch-shape sensitivity at verify (1+N) shape).
}

-- Verifies a draft block against the target. The verify batch
-- [anchor, t_0, ..., t_{N-1}] is a single contiguous run at
-- positions [anchor_pos, anchor_pos+1, ..., anchor_pos+block_size];
-- the target consumes it in one forward pass and returns
-- per-position logits used by AcceptPrefixDecision.
--
-- The contract takes a VerifyBatch (which records anchor +
-- block_size + tokens together) rather than the (block, anchor)
-- pair. Either form is computationally equivalent; VerifyBatch
-- makes the canonical input shape explicit and is what
-- ConstructVerifyBatch (out of scope here; trivially derivable
-- from DraftBlock + AnchorToken) would emit.
contract TargetVerifyBlock {
    invoke: (
        target: TargetModel,
        batch: VerifyBatch,
        target_kv: TargetKVCache,
    ) -> VerifyLogits

    @invariant VerifyBatchShape
        -- VerifyLogits.n_positions = block.block_size + 1. The
        -- target consumes anchor + block; it emits one logit row
        -- per input position. Row 0 predicts next-after-anchor
        -- (corresponds to draft t_0). Row k predicts
        -- next-after-t_{k-1}.

    @invariant SingleContiguousRun
        -- The verify batch is one contiguous run in seq_id = block
        -- owner's seq_id. No multi-slot batching. (Under np=1
        -- production, this is trivially the case; np>1 with DFlash
        -- is out of scope of this spec.)

    @invariant TargetKVNotAdvancedDuringVerify
        -- Verify runs against the target's KV state at
        -- target_kv.n_cells = anchor_pos + 1 (the state AFTER the
        -- anchor was committed). The verify forward does NOT mutate
        -- target_kv; KV advancement happens later in AdvanceState
        -- and only by the accepted prefix.
        --
        -- Implementations that write KV during the verify forward
        -- must roll back the rejected suffix before AdvanceState
        -- completes; the net mutation is exactly the accepted
        -- prefix.

    @invariant PerSlotVerifyDispatchAtMultiSlot
        -- At n_parallel > 1, the verify forward is dispatched
        -- per-slot (|B|=1 in every transformer compute call), NOT
        -- as a single batched forward over all slots. Each slot's
        -- verify runs on its own contiguous (anchor + block_size)
        -- positions, producing its own VerifyLogits independently.
        --
        -- Rationale: the PHASE45 D10.e investigation
        -- (project_mtp_multislot_determinism_investigation_failed
        -- memory entry) could not pin down whether the
        -- multi-slot-batched-verify divergence on Qwen 3.6 27B was
        -- on-target-MTP-specific or a general target property. Until
        -- empirical resolution of OQ-DFLASH-INHERITS-MTP-MULTISLOT-BUG,
        -- per-slot verify is the only path with byte-deterministic
        -- output across slots.
        --
        -- Batched verify (single forward over (1+block_size)*n_parallel
        -- positions) is a Gate-7+ perf optimization, conditional on
        -- the empirical result coming back GREEN. Until then, per-slot
        -- dispatch is the only supported path.

    @invariant DeterminismPerDeployment
        -- Two TargetVerifyBlock invocations with byte-identical
        -- (target, block, target_kv, anchor) produce byte-identical
        -- VerifyLogits. Block-shape sensitivity is a known kernel
        -- surface (cf. multi-slot determinism investigation memory
        -- entry); per-deployment with fixed block_size, runs are
        -- bit-stable.

    @invariant EffectiveSeqLensSubtractsRejected
        -- In padded-batch mode, cad.seq_lens includes positions
        -- corresponding to rejected tokens from the previous
        -- accept step (those positions still exist in the slot
        -- block table even though their KV must be overwritten).
        -- Before attention runs on the verify batch, the impl
        -- MUST compute:
        --   effective_seq_lens = cad.seq_lens - num_rejected_tokens
        -- and pass effective_seq_lens (not raw cad.seq_lens) into
        -- the attention metadata.
        --
        -- Otherwise the attention sees stale rejected-suffix
        -- positions as live context and the verify logits drift
        -- arbitrarily from the trained model's expectations.
        --
        -- Provenance: vllm dflash.py:283-287 explicit calc
        --   "In padded mode, cad.seq_lens includes rejected tokens.
        --    Subtract them so attention only sees the valid prefix
        --    of context states."
}

-- Decides how many drafts to accept and what bonus token to commit,
-- given verify logits over the drafted block. Pure host-side
-- computation; no GPU state mutation.
contract AcceptPrefixDecision {
    invoke: (
        block: DraftBlock,
        logits: VerifyLogits,
        sampler: SamplerMode,
        mode: AcceptMode,
    ) -> AcceptDecision

    @invariant LongestPrefixMatchUnderArgmax
        -- mode = argmax_match implies n_accepted is the largest k
        -- in [0, block.block_size] such that for every i in [0, k):
        -- block.tokens[i] = argmax(logits at row i). Ties in argmax
        -- broken by lowest token id.

    @invariant NAcceptedWithinBound
        -- 0 <= n_accepted <= block.block_size.

    @invariant BonusIsArgmaxAtFirstUnacceptedRow
        -- bonus_token = argmax(logits at row n_accepted), ties
        -- broken by lowest token id. The bonus is committed
        -- regardless of n_accepted; if n_accepted = block_size,
        -- the bonus comes from the last logit row (predicting
        -- next-after-last-accepted-draft).

    @invariant BonusPosIsAnchorPlusNAcceptedPlusOne
        -- bonus_pos = block.anchor_pos + n_accepted + 1. The bonus
        -- token occupies the position immediately after the last
        -- accepted draft (or after the anchor if zero accepted).

    @invariant DeterminismUnderFixedInputs
        -- Pure function of inputs. Two invocations with byte-
        -- identical (block, logits, sampler, mode) produce
        -- byte-identical AcceptDecision.

    @invariant ProbabilisticVerifyOutOfScope
        -- mode = probabilistic and sampler = probabilistic are
        -- rejected at the contract boundary in the initial
        -- 2026-q2-next implementation. Greedy-only at first
        -- landing; expand once the greedy path is shipped and
        -- measured.

    @invariant NumRejectedTokensFlowsBackToProposer
        -- After AcceptPrefixDecision returns AcceptDecision, the
        -- value (block.block_size - decision.n_accepted) is the
        -- number of rejected drafts. This count MUST be passed
        -- forward into the next DraftBlockEmit cycle's input
        -- preparation as num_rejected_tokens, so that:
        --   (1) draft KV slots corresponding to rejected positions
        --       are overwritten rather than treated as live context,
        --   (2) effective_seq_lens in the next verify can subtract
        --       the rejected count (see
        --       EffectiveSeqLensSubtractsRejected),
        --   (3) the anchor for the next cycle is the bonus token at
        --       block.anchor_pos + decision.n_accepted + 1 (see
        --       BonusPosIsAnchorPlusNAcceptedPlusOne).
        --
        -- Implementations that drop the rejected-count between
        -- cycles produce subtly wrong attention as soon as a
        -- non-full accept occurs.
        --
        -- Provenance: vllm dflash.py:211 (num_rejected_tokens_gpu
        --   parameter of set_inputs_first_pass), :262 (passed into
        --   kernel call), :286 (used to compute effective_seq_lens).
}

-- Advances target and draft KV caches by the accepted prefix +
-- bonus, evicts the rejected tail from the draft KV, and produces
-- the new anchor for the next cycle. The single source of state
-- change after one speculative cycle.
contract AdvanceState {
    invoke: (
        decision: AcceptDecision,
        block: DraftBlock,
        target_kv: TargetKVCache,
        draft_kv: DraftKVCache,
    ) -> AnchorToken

    @invariant TargetKVAdvancesByAcceptedPlusBonus
        -- target_kv.n_cells (after) = target_kv.n_cells (before) +
        -- decision.n_accepted + 1. The +1 is the bonus, which is
        -- always committed.

    @invariant DraftKVAdvancesPaired
        -- draft_kv.n_cells_self (after) = draft_kv.n_cells_self
        -- (before) + decision.n_accepted + 1. The drafter's own
        -- autoregressive state advances by the same amount as the
        -- target's: every committed token contributes a KV cell
        -- on both sides.

    @invariant DraftKVRollbackOnRejection
        -- If the drafter's verify-time forward wrote KV cells for
        -- the full block_size, the implementation must drop cells
        -- (n_accepted .. block_size-1) from draft_kv before the
        -- next cycle. The drafter never sees the rejected tail
        -- again.

    @invariant InjectedKVEvictedOnAnchorAdvance
        -- draft_kv.n_cells_injected decreases by the number of
        -- InjectedKV anchors whose anchor_pos < new_anchor.pos.
        -- Stale fused features for past anchors are evicted as
        -- soon as the anchor moves past them.

    @invariant NewAnchorIsBonus
        -- The returned AnchorToken has token_id = decision.bonus_token
        -- and pos = decision.bonus_pos. The next cycle's
        -- ExtractFeatures runs against the new anchor.

    @invariant AtomicityPerCycle
        -- AdvanceState is the single mutation point per
        -- speculative cycle. Implementations must not partially
        -- advance: either all four side-effects (target KV, draft
        -- self KV, draft injected KV eviction, new anchor) happen
        -- consistently, or the cycle fails and no state changes.
        -- This is the rollback boundary if any step fails.
}

-- ============================================================
-- System-wide invariants — cross-contract obligations
-- ============================================================

-- Targets and drafters share the embedding and LM head tensors. The
-- drafter GGUF must declare a reference to the target's embed and
-- head; the loader must materialise a single underlying tensor for
-- both models. Doubling these would waste ~5 GiB at BF16 for
-- vocab=248320 × hidden=5120 × 2 (embed + head).
invariant SharedEmbedAndLMHead {
    -- TargetModel.embedding === DraftModel.embedding (same
    -- underlying memory). TargetModel.lm_head ===
    -- DraftModel.lm_head. The convert pipeline that produces the
    -- DFlash GGUF must encode this sharing; the runtime must honour
    -- it.
}

-- Feature extraction layers are a fixed subset, deterministic per
-- deployment. Changing the subset between sessions yields different
-- drafter behaviour even with identical weights.
invariant FeatureSourceFixedPerDeployment {
    -- HiddenFeatures.source_indices is a deployment-time constant.
    -- Mid-session changes are forbidden.
}

-- block_size is fixed at context creation and must match the
-- value the drafter was trained at. vLLM allows per-KV-group
-- runtime override via kernel_block_sizes (qwen3_dflash.py:267),
-- but that's a perf-tuning lever for vLLM's block manager; it
-- does not change the drafter's trained block_size, which is
-- a model-architecture constant.
invariant BlockSizeFixedAtContextStart {
    -- block_size = drafter GGUF metadata dflash.block_size at
    -- llama_set_dflash() time. It is read once and locked for
    -- the context's lifetime. CLI override --dflash-block-size
    -- exists for experimentation but must equal the GGUF value
    -- or load fails with LLAMA_DFLASH_BLOCK_SIZE_MISMATCH.
    -- Mid-session reconfiguration is forbidden — the drafter's
    -- positional mask construction and verify-batch shape
    -- contract both depend on block_size being constant within
    -- the context.
}

-- Per-deployment determinism: greedy + fixed block_size + fixed
-- feature source = byte-identical outputs across runs. Cross-
-- deployment (different block_size, different source layers) is
-- explicitly NOT bit-stable; the kernel batch-shape sensitivity
-- captured in the multi-slot investigation memory entry applies to
-- the (anchor + block_size) verify batch in the same way it
-- applied to multi-slot verify batches.
invariant PerDeploymentDeterminism {
    -- Under SamplerMode = greedy and AcceptMode = argmax_match,
    -- two runs with identical (TargetModel state, DraftModel
    -- state, block_size, source_indices) produce byte-identical
    -- token streams. Across runs that differ in block_size or
    -- source_indices, outputs may differ.
}

-- The speculative cycle is atomic. Within a cycle, the order is:
--   ExtractFeatures → ProjectAndFuse → DraftBlockEmit →
--   TargetVerifyBlock → AcceptPrefixDecision → AdvanceState.
-- Implementations may pipeline or overlap on-GPU, but the host-side
-- observable state changes only at the end of AdvanceState.
invariant SpeculativeCycleAtomicity {
    -- A cycle either completes fully (AdvanceState commits) or
    -- fails and reverts to the state at cycle start. No partial
    -- KV writes, no half-committed bonus tokens.
}

-- Sync barrier — a slot's cycle counter advances only when its
-- in-flight stream is no longer running. Prevents reading
-- pre-completion KV state on the next cycle.
--
-- Provenance: lifted from specs/multislot/StreamFix.tla — equivalent
-- to F3 (StepDoesNotAdvanceWithRunningStream) from PHASE45 work.
-- Bound by TLA+ invariant SyncBeforeStepAdvance in
-- specs/dflash/DFlashMultiSlot.tla.
invariant SyncBeforeStepAdvance {
    -- For every slot s and every cycle transition:
    --   step[s] post-AdvanceState > step[s] pre-AdvanceState
    --   => stream_status[s] != "running" between the two.
    -- Implementation: server's per-slot SyncBarrier action waits
    -- for all of that slot's in-flight CUDA streams before issuing
    -- the next per-slot dispatch.
}

-- Cross-slot KV-write-region disjointness — at any moment in time,
-- no two slots' in-flight KV writes share a write region. Together
-- with PerSlotDraftKVCache this gives slot-level serialisation
-- without locks (regions are seq_id-keyed; the per-slot stream
-- never touches another slot's regions).
--
-- Provenance: lifted from specs/multislot/StreamFix.tla
-- NoCrossStreamRace; re-verified for DFlash's three-region-per-slot
-- layout (target_kv, draft_kv_self, draft_kv_injected). Bound by
-- TLA+ invariant NoCrossSlotRegionOverlap in
-- specs/dflash/DFlashMultiSlot.tla.
invariant NoCrossSlotRegionOverlap {
    -- For all distinct slots s, t with stream_status[s] = "running"
    -- and stream_status[t] = "running":
    --   in_flight_writes[s] \cap in_flight_writes[t] = {}
    --
    -- Modeled regions per slot: { target_kv, draft_kv_self,
    -- draft_kv_injected }. The TLA model in DFlashMultiSlot.tla
    -- exhaustively explores |Slots| = 2..4 and finds no
    -- counterexample under PerSlot dispatch.
    --
    -- Violation symptom (per CrossSlotRace negative control): a
    -- StartStreamWithBugD action models the bug where slot s's
    -- stream writes into slot t's KV regions. TLC catches this
    -- in 33 states at depth ~10. ik_llama.cpp implementation must
    -- have the per-slot KV-region partitioning structurally
    -- enforced (each kv_cache lives under its slot's seq_id with
    -- no aliasing).
}

-- The drafter is implemented via KV-injection, not via T5-style
-- cross-attention. Per-anchor target features are projected through
-- the drafter's per-layer wk/wv weights and written to the drafter's
-- own K/V cache; the drafter then runs plain self-attention against
-- that cache. The encoder/decoder dual-context pattern used by
-- upstream llama.cpp PR #22105 is explicitly rejected here.
invariant DraftKVViaInjectionNotCrossAttention {
    -- Rationale (see PHASE_DFLASH_DESIGN.md §"Core decision"):
    --   - Cross-attention has graph-reuse=0 cost (cross.n_enc grows
    --     monotonically; the encoder graph rebuilds every step).
    --     Upstream PR #22105's own "Future Performance Work"
    --     flags this as the dominant cost.
    --   - At our context scales (np=8 × ctx=64k), cross-attention
    --     storage is ~10x what KV-injection requires
    --     (5 source layers × 5120 hidden × 2 bytes per anchor =
    --     10 KiB per commit × 64k commits × 8 slots = 5 GiB;
    --     KV-injection stores ~0.7 GiB at the same configuration).
    --   - KV-injection produces a stable drafter forward shape
    --     across cycles, CUDA-graph-cache-friendly.
    -- The implementation enforces this at the architecture-handler
    -- level: dflash arch builds a self-attention drafter graph with
    -- its own KV cache, not an encoder-decoder pair.
}

-- The drafter holds n_parallel sets of K/V cache slots, one per
-- active sequence. Each slot's cache is independently keyed by
-- its seq_id and contains the K/V derived from that slot's anchor
-- history.
invariant PerSlotDraftKVCache {
    -- DraftKVCache.seq_id partitions storage. Multi-slot serving
    -- with shared drafter cache slots is forbidden — that would
    -- re-introduce cross-slot KV pollution analogous to what the
    -- D10.e investigation could not rule out for target KV.
    -- Each per-slot drafter K/V cache is sized:
    --   - SWA layers: window_size cells per slot (independent of ctx)
    --   - full-attention layer: ctx-per-slot cells per slot
    -- For Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash (4 SWA + 1 full, window=2048),
    -- per-slot KV is dominated by the full-attention layer and
    -- scales linearly with ctx-per-slot.
}

-- Hybrid target's recurrent state (DeltaNet / linear_attention
-- layers) requires per-slot tracking with ping-pong buffering at
-- n_parallel > 1 + overlap scheduling. Qwen 3.6 27B has 48 of 64
-- layers as linear_attention; each maintains a recurrent state that
-- must not be corrupted by interleaved draft/verify cycles across
-- slots. SGLang's HybridReqToTokenPool (memory_pool.py:540-735)
-- implements this via req_index_to_mamba_ping_pong_track_buffer_mapping
-- with size 2 for overlap and size 1 for non-overlap. ik_llama.cpp's
-- implementation must provide an equivalent at any multi-slot
-- configuration on a hybrid target — even without overlap scheduling
-- (size 1 is still tracked, in case rejection forces a state revert).
invariant HybridTargetRecurrentStateTracking {
    -- For each slot s, the target's recurrent (linear_attention /
    -- DeltaNet) state is partitioned by seq_id and tracked through
    -- the speculative cycle:
    --
    --   - Per-slot recurrent state is saved before the verify
    --     forward (the verify may mutate the state through all
    --     block_size positions optimistically).
    --   - On rejection of any draft beyond accept_prefix, the
    --     recurrent state at positions > accept_prefix MUST be
    --     reverted before the next cycle's verify uses it as
    --     input.
    --
    -- The block_size=16 verify in DFlash makes this 16x more
    -- aggressive than np=1 MTP's --draft 3 (which only had 3 draft
    -- positions to potentially revert). At np=8 the system handles
    -- up to 128 simultaneous in-flight recurrent-state writes that
    -- may need reverting.
    --
    -- Without this tracking, a rejected slot's recurrent state
    -- contaminates the next cycle's draft, breaking determinism
    -- per-deployment.
}

-- Distributed parallelism mode constraints. The target+drafter
-- pair assumes co-located devices for KV cache sharing and
-- attention computation order. SGLang enforces these at
-- server_args.py:3247-3306.
invariant DPAttentionNotSupported {
    -- Data-parallel attention (DP) changes the attention computation
    -- order in ways that DFlash's mask shapes don't survive.
    -- llama_set_dflash() must reject any configuration that enables
    -- DP attention (return LLAMA_DFLASH_DP_NOT_SUPPORTED) at bind
    -- time. ik_llama.cpp currently doesn't have DP attention; this
    -- invariant is forward-looking.
}

invariant PipelineParallelismRequiresPpSizeEq1 {
    -- DFlash assumes target and drafter models are co-located on
    -- the same device(s); pipeline parallelism (pp_size > 1)
    -- spreads layers across devices and breaks the K/V cache
    -- sharing contract between drafter K/V (per-anchor injected)
    -- and target K/V (per-bonus committed). Reject at bind if
    -- pp_size > 1.
}

-- Memory budget at multi-slot must fit the host hardware. Production
-- 2× Quadro RTX 6000 has 48 GiB aggregate VRAM. Target weights,
-- drafter weights, target KV (scales with np × ctx-per-slot for
-- full-attention layers), drafter KV (mostly window-bounded),
-- and compute scratch all share this budget.
invariant ContextBudgetAtNp8 {
    -- For Qwen3.6-27B target on 2× RTX 6000 at n_parallel = 8:
    --   - Target weights (Q-loose / IQ4_KS): ~28 GiB
    --   - Drafter weights (BF16): ~3.5 GiB
    --   - Target KV (16 full-attention layers × KV per slot):
    --     dominant scaling cost
    --   - Drafter KV: ~10% of target KV at every scale
    --   - Compute + sched + NCCL: ~3 GiB
    -- This bounds ctx-per-slot ≤ ~64k at np=8 with q4_0+hadamard
    -- KV; ctx=128k requires np≤4; ctx=256k requires np≤2 (and even
    -- np=2 at 256k is tight).
    -- The production profile for np=8 must declare
    -- max-model-len ≤ 65536 to stay within budget.
}

-- The drafter is architecturally dense Qwen3 (not hybrid). vLLM
-- enforces this at load (`_DFLASH_VALID_LAYER_TYPES = {full_attention,
-- sliding_attention}` in `qwen3_dflash.py:55`). We bind the same
-- contract: if a loaded drafter declares any `linear_attention`
-- (DeltaNet) layer type, fail at load.
invariant DrafterIsDenseQwen3 {
    -- For every layer index i in [0, DraftModel.n_layers):
    -- DraftModel.layer_types[i] ∈ {full_attention, sliding_attention}.
    -- Reject load on any other value.
}

-- DFlash drafter and target share token-id space exactly. Anything
-- in the target's vocab the drafter must be able to draft; anything
-- the drafter drafts the target must verify. No extra or missing
-- token ids. This is what makes shared embed/LM head sound.
invariant DrafterTargetVocabIdentity {
    -- TargetModel.vocab_size = DraftModel.vocab_size (where the
    -- drafter inherits the target's vocab via the converter's
    -- --target-model-dir mechanism). Verified at GGUF load.
}

-- Drafter has no vision tower. Multimodal turns (prompts containing
-- image or video tokens) must bypass the DFlash speculative path
-- and decode against the bare target. The drafter's logits at
-- vision-special-token positions (e.g. Qwen3.6-27B's
-- image_token_id=248056, video_token_id=248057) are
-- statistical-noise quality because the drafter never saw vision
-- attention; rejecting them at verify is wasted work; routing
-- multimodal around the drafter is the correct shape.
--
-- Note: vLLM PR #40898 has a no-op _warn_if_multimodal override
-- (dflash.py:120-124) that allows multimodal inputs without
-- implementing actual routing. ik_llama.cpp must implement the
-- bypass at the SERVER / caller layer, not rely on inheritance —
-- this is a real implementation effort, not a no-op.
invariant MultimodalTurnsRoutedAroundDrafter {
    -- If the incoming prompt contains any of the target's vision
    -- token ids (vision_start, vision_end, image_token_id,
    -- video_token_id), the speculative-decoding path is bypassed
    -- for that request. The server-level router must detect this
    -- before the speculative loop starts and route the request
    -- through bare-target decode. Returning
    -- LLAMA_DFLASH_MULTIMODAL_PROMPT from llama_dflash_draft_*
    -- if the caller failed to route is the defensive fallback.
}

-- The hidden-feature extraction count matches what the drafter
-- was trained against. The paper (§5) uses 5 source layers
-- uniformly selected between layer 2 and the third-to-last target
-- layer. Both the upstream llama.cpp PR and vLLM hardcode an
-- assumption of len(target_layer_ids) == 5; ik_llama.cpp's
-- implementation must read this from GGUF metadata and apply
-- without assumption.
invariant SourceLayerCountMatchesDrafterTraining {
    -- HiddenFeatures.n_source_layers equals the count declared
    -- in the drafter GGUF metadata key dflash.target_layer_ids.
    -- For Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash this is expected to be 5; the
    -- implementation must not hardcode 5.
}

-- Cross-engine convention: dflash_config.target_layer_ids in the
-- HF drafter config refers to "the layer whose post-output we want
-- as a feature". The runtime extract hook fires at the residual
-- stream entering the NEXT layer (one position later). Both
-- llama.cpp's converter (convert_hf_to_gguf.py:4913) and vLLM's
-- algos.py apply a `+1` shift when translating
-- dflash_config.target_layer_ids → runtime extract indices.
invariant TargetLayerIdsPlusOneAtRuntime {
    -- Runtime extract index i_runtime = dflash_config_index + 1.
    -- The GGUF metadata stored by the converter is the runtime
    -- index (already shifted). Implementations that read the GGUF
    -- value directly are correct; implementations that re-read the
    -- HF config must apply +1.
}

-- DFlash does not do tree drafting. SGLang enforces num_steps==1
-- and eagle_topk==1 (server_args.py:3272, 3281). Block emit
-- produces ONE block at the bonus's position; no fan-out, no
-- multi-branch.
invariant NoTreeDraftingNoChainRollout {
    -- One DraftBlockEmit per cycle; one block; no parallel
    -- draft branches.
}

-- ============================================================
-- Open questions for 2026-q2-next implementation
-- ============================================================

open question "OQ-SOURCE-LAYERS [RESOLVED 2026-05-11]: drafter config (data/dflash-27b-config/config.json) declares dflash_config.target_layer_ids = [1, 16, 31, 46, 61]. Five sources across 64 target layers per build_target_layer_ids(num_target_layers=64, num_draft_layers=5) at github.com/z-lab/dflash dflash/model.py:27 — uniform spacing on [1, num_target-3] = [1, 61]. ik_llama.cpp reads from GGUF metadata at load; no CLI override."

open question "OQ-DRAFTER-CONFIG-GATED [RESOLVED 2026-05-11]: gate accepted on HF for slartibardfast0; config.json fetched and preserved at data/dflash-27b-config/config.json. Drafter confirmed: 5 hidden layers, hidden_size=5120 (matches target — SharedEmbedAndLMHead sound), head_dim=128, num_attention_heads=32, num_key_value_heads=8 (GQA ratio 4 within drafter), intermediate_size=17408, vocab_size=248320 (matches target), max_position_embeddings=262144, rope_theta=10000000 (matches target — vLLM's 1M default would be wrong), tie_word_embeddings=false, dtype=bfloat16, sliding_window=2048, use_sliding_window=true, layer_types=[sliding,sliding,sliding,sliding,full], block_size=16, mask_token_id=248070, target_layer_ids=[1,16,31,46,61]."

open question "OQ-HYBRID-TARGET-EXTRACT [RESOLVED 2026-05-11]: prior concern (drafter trained against pre-DeltaNet residuals?) was unfounded. The z-lab reference impl at github.com/z-lab/dflash dflash/model.py:39-45 extracts features via hidden_states[layer_id + offset] with offset=1, where hidden_states comes from transformers' output.hidden_states (length n_layers+1, index 0 = embeddings, index k = post-layer-(k-1) output). So target_layer_ids=[1,16,31,46,61] extracts post-layer-1, post-layer-16, post-layer-31, post-layer-46, post-layer-61 outputs (post-DeltaNet-and-FFN with residual). Upstream llama.cpp's +1-shift convention places the runtime extract hook (cb(inpL,..., il)) at inpL of layer N+1, which equals post-layer-N output — same site. No silent risk."

open question "OQ-DENOISE-SCHEDULE: single-step is the only schedule the published method measures. The drafter weights are trained for single-step denoising. Multi-step is admissible by the architecture but not by the trained weights; out of scope for 2026-q2-next."

open question "OQ-BLOCK-SIZE-FOR-TURING [RESOLVED 2026-05-11; refined with paper finding]: ship at block_size=16 (drafter's trained value) to match training exactly. Paper §5.4.4 explicitly states: 'A model trained with a larger block size generalizes well to smaller inference-time block sizes' — so block_size=8 at inference is a *paper-blessed* fallback if Gate-5 shows FA non-determinism at ne[1]=17 on sm_75. (The reverse — trained-smaller, infer-larger — does NOT generalize, so we cannot go above 16.) Decision order: (a) ship at 16; (b) if Gate-5 binds RED at ne[1]=17, specialise FA dispatch for that shape OR fall back to block_size=8 (cite paper §5.4.4)."

open question "OQ-QUANT-MIX: production target runs at IQ4_KS. The drafter ships BF16. The convert path that ik_llama.cpp eventually grows must support the cross-model SharedEmbedAndLMHead invariant when the two models declare different quants for the shared tensors. PHASE_DFLASH_DESIGN.md commits to materialising shared embed/lm_head from the target's IQ4_KS tensor; drafter never re-quantizes."

open question "OQ-SWA-WINDOW [RESOLVED 2026-05-11]: drafter config declares sliding_window=2048 and layer_types=[sliding_attention, sliding_attention, sliding_attention, sliding_attention, full_attention]. 4 SWA layers + 1 full attention layer (the last, layer index 4). use_sliding_window=true. ik_llama.cpp reads these per-layer from drafter GGUF metadata at load; surface via llama_dflash_swa_window(model, layer_idx) which returns 2048 for layer_idx ∈ [0,3] and -1 for layer_idx=4 (full_attention)."

open question "OQ-WINDOW-CONVENTION [RESOLVED 2026-05-11 by source read of installed vLLM PR #40898]: vLLM passes sliding_window as the literal window size to FlashAttention's per-layer per_layer_sliding_window parameter (qwen3_dflash.py:172, :237). FlashAttention's documented convention for that parameter is the standard 'attend to [max(0, k-W+1), k]' interpretation. dflash.py:423-444 enforces per-layer-type mask metadata: sliding_attention layers get causal=True, all others get causal=False — assertion guards on both sides confirm the contract. Conclusion: ik_llama.cpp adopts the literal-window convention (2048 = literal window size for Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash SWA layers). SGLang's window_left = sliding_window - 1 in dflash_utils.py:321 is an SGLang-internal off-by-one transformation; vLLM and llama.cpp pass through unchanged. The training-time convention question is dissolved by the empirical fact that vLLM's source uses the literal value with no transformation and the model owner (z-lab) co-authored that PR."

open question "OQ-INTRA-BLOCK-MASK [RESOLVED 2026-05-11]: confirmed via vLLM PR #40898 (vllm/v1/spec_decode/dflash.py:435-444 assertion block + lines 410, 428, 304 with causal flags and use_non_causal=True). The drafter uses a layer-type-dependent mask: sliding_attention layers run causal SWA (causal=True, asserted); full_attention layers run bidirectional (causal=False, asserted). For Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash specifically (layer_types=[sliding,sliding,sliding,sliding,full]), layers 0-3 are causal-SWA window=2048, layer 4 is bidirectional. Bidirectional mixing happens at the final layer — that is where block-diffusion denoising sees all mask positions together. The spec's prior CausalSWAMaskWithinBlock invariant was wrong and has been replaced by LayerTypeDependentMask. SGLang's custom_mask=None default-to-causal across all layers does NOT match the trained model and is a likely reason SGLang's accept rates run lower than vLLM's on the same drafter."

open question "OQ-MASK-TOKEN-SEMANTICS [RESOLVED 2026-05-11]: drafter config.dflash_config.mask_token_id = 248070. Target Qwen3.6-27B tokenizer (data/dflash-27b-config/ companion) maps token 248070 to '<|audio_start|>' — a multimodal sentinel from the target's vocab that goes unused in pure-text contexts. Z-lab chose it as the drafter's mask sentinel for that reason. The drafter consumes 248070 as input only at masked positions during block-emit; if it ever emits 248070 in greedy draft logits the verify pass rejects it (the target's text-only contexts don't predict audio sentinels). No production concern."

open question "OQ-BLOCK-SIZE-MISMATCH-AT-INFERENCE [RESOLVED 2026-05-11 by deciding to match training]: superseded by OQ-BLOCK-SIZE-FOR-TURING resolution to ship at block_size=16. The mismatch was a hypothetical concern about running at 8 vs trained 16; that concern is moot because we are not running at 8. The Gate-5 binding test for FA kernel determinism at ne[1]=17 absorbs the remaining uncertainty."

open question "OQ-THINK-MODE-EQUIVALENT: the upstream PR records LLAMA_SPEC_NO_THINK as a significant accept-rate lever for Qwen3-family targets. Our production server uses a Jinja chat template; the equivalent control on this stack is whether the prompt enables the thinking sentinel. PHASE_DFLASH_DESIGN.md commits to a new CLI flag --dflash-think on|off with default off matching upstream's measurement."

open question "OQ-MULTI-SLOT [REVISED 2026-05-11]: design supports n_parallel up to 8 from day one via per-slot dispatch (see PerSlotVerifyDispatchAtMultiSlot, PerSlotDraftKVCache, ContextBudgetAtNp8). The PHASE45 D10.e investigation could not pin down whether the multi-slot determinism gap was on-target-MTP-specific or a general target property — DFlash uses zero on-target MTP code, so the empirical test (OQ-DFLASH-INHERITS-MTP-MULTISLOT-BUG) is meaningful and cheap. Per-slot dispatch is the correctness baseline. Batched verify (single forward over (1+block_size)*n_parallel positions, reusing the multi-slot batched amortization that the abandoned MTP per-slot work also wanted) becomes a Gate-7+ optimization conditional on that empirical result coming back GREEN."

open question "OQ-DFLASH-INHERITS-MTP-MULTISLOT-BUG [RESOLVED 2026-05-12 — GREEN]: Gate-3.5 ran successfully on vLLM PR #40898 + z-lab/Qwen3.6-27B-DFlash + Qwen3.6-27B target, 2× RTX 6000 (sm_75), fp16, tp=2, cpu_offload_gb=12, with 3 runtime sm_75 monkey-patches (combine_hidden_states dtype cast, FlexAttention .view→.reshape, FlexAttention BLOCK_M/N largest POW2 divisor). Same prompt, greedy decode (temperature=0, seed=42), 96 tokens each, 5 streams compared: A (np=1), B[0]+B[1] (two identical requests in np=2 batch), C[0]+C[1] (np=2 rerun for self-stability). **All 5 streams byte-identical, n_diff_pairs=0, verdict GREEN.** See data/gate35-dflash-determinism.json for raw data. DFlash with vLLM's single-batched-grid kernel dispatch (grid=(batch_size, num_blocks)) does NOT inherit the byte-level non-determinism that bit PHASE45 D10.e MTP multi-slot. The dispatch shape class that broke MTP works correctly for DFlash on this hardware/path. Caveats: result is for fp16+3-patches not yet upstream; np=2 on one prompt is not a proof of np≤8 across all shapes. PerSlotVerifyDispatchAtMultiSlot remains the spec ceiling (stronger than this single empirical result)."

open question "OQ-VLLM-PR-MERGE-RISK: the reference impls (vLLM PR #40898, SGLang PR #23000, upstream llama.cpp PR #22105) are all draft. PHASE_DFLASH_DESIGN.md commits to anchoring on the published paper plus our design, not on upstream's PR; upstream PR is reference only and may pivot without affecting our work."

open question "OQ-FAILURE-MODE-ON-MISSING-DRAFT: what happens if the drafter fails to emit a coherent block (e.g. the model returns NaN, or the injected K/V slot is missing for an active anchor)? At first landing the choice is hard failure with logged context, matching MTP-IR. Move to graceful fallback to non-speculative decode after the path is shipped and measured."
